    "As mentioned earlier, collision detection becomes more complex when objects are closer together.",
    "Additionally, in such close proximity, even small movements can significantly change the computational load.",
    "Thus, when objects are near each other, an RL agent, through small and continuous movements, can better understand which types of movements will lead to greater computational load and execution time in different situations.",
    "RL vs. Random AlgorithmThe statistical analysis comparing RL PPO ED and RL A2C ED with the random algorithm for the CD case study produced significant results, with all pvalues being close to 0.",
